<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 2:55AM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern Walker,
east central Tuscaloosa, northeastern Bibb and western Jefferson
Counties through 345 AM CDT...
At 255 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Burnwell to near North Bibb. Movement was north
at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Birmingham, Bessemer, Hueytown, Fairfield, Sumiton,
Cordova, Dora, Pleasant Grove, Midfield, Adamsville, Brighton,
Lipscomb, Graysville, Lake View, Sylvan Springs, Woodstock,
Brookside, Mulga, Sipsey and Maytown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
